SmartForge application-database migrations (Alembic, single database).

Scope: the transactional `app` database ONLY. The analytics `warehouse`
database is NOT managed here — its schemas/roles/control tables are
provisioned idempotently by `python -m app.dataplatform.cli bootstrap`,
its raw tables by dlt, and its models by dbt (see ../../../specs/ARCHITECTURE.md).

Workflow (full guide: backend/README.md "Migrations"):
  docker compose exec backend bash
  alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe the change"
  alembic upgrade head

Rules of the road:
  * Migrations run automatically before the backend starts (the compose
    `prestart` service / Helm pre-install+pre-upgrade hook Job runs
    `scripts/prestart.sh`).
  * Keep migrations backward-compatible one release back: `helm rollback`
    re-runs the hook but never downgrades the schema.
  * Commit every generated revision under versions/.
